+## Required Options
+
+Pass `required=True` to make an option mandatory. A required option is marked
+with `[required]` in the options listing and is spelled out in the usage line
+instead of being summarized by the bracketed `[OPTIONS]` placeholder, so it is
+visible at a glance which options must be provided.
+
+```{eval-rst}
+.. click:example::
+
+    @click.command()
+    @click.option('--name', required=True, help='Who to greet.')
+    @click.option('--greeting', default='Hello', help='How to greet.')
+    def greet(name, greeting):
+        click.echo(f"{greeting}, {name}!")
+
+.. click:run::
+
+    invoke(greet, args=['--help'])
+
+.. click:run::
+
+    invoke(greet, args=[])
+```
+
